<h3 class="date"><a href="/2006/oct/03/">&#x27a0;</a> October 3, 2006</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="listening_post" >

        
        <a name="002969"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://blog.wired.com/music/index.blog?entry_id=1563889">Listening Post: Winamp Adds Remote Access, Dashboard Widgets</a></h4>

        

        <p>New version of WinAmp (Remember them?  It&#8217;s like an iPod, except you can&#8217;t carry it around with you.  Ask your parents) includes &#8220;remote listening&#8221; &#8212; Stream music from your home PC to wherevers.  Since Apple kept disabling hacks that did this with iTunes, I&#8217;m curious how AOL think they&#8217;re going to be able to keep this &#8220;legit&#8221;</p>

